1
00:00:01,370 --> 00:00:02,440
Thank you, come again.

2
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:03,710
(Episode 45)

3
00:00:05,140 --> 00:00:06,850
I'm in such a foul mood.

4
00:00:07,980 --> 00:00:10,280
Nothing seems to make me feel better.

5
00:00:10,820 --> 00:00:12,320
Shit, this is so frustrating!

6
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:02,730
How can she look exactly like me?
What on earth is going on?

7
00:01:07,370 --> 00:01:08,740
Excuse me! Wait a second.

8
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:10,240
Hey, you!

9
00:01:12,410 --> 00:01:15,610
What now? What am I supposed to do
if we meet face-to-face?

10
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,520
Excuse me! Hey!

11
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:22,350
Am I seeing things?

12
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:23,690
No, it can't be.

13
00:01:24,390 --> 00:01:25,390
Hey!

14
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:30,060
Excuse me.

15
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Excuse me.

16
00:01:32,630 --> 00:01:33,770
Listen...

17
00:01:34,470 --> 00:01:37,540
I know this might be a bit forward
since we’ve just met,

18
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:39,140
but could you look at me for a moment?

19
00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:48,610
How...

20
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:52,320
- How can we look so much alike?
- Tell me about it.

21
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:56,350
Why do we look so much alike?

22
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,160
How is this possible?

23
00:01:58,690 --> 00:01:59,760
Who are you?

24
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:02,730
I know exactly how you feel.

25
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:05,630
I was just as confused as you are.

26
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:28,650
It's like I'm looking in a mirror.

27
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:34,190
This isn't a dream, right?

28
00:02:39,430 --> 00:02:42,400
So you're the type who has to feel it
to believe it.

29
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:45,300
My name is Oh Jang Mi.

30
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:46,940
And you are?

31
00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:51,180
If Oh Jang Mi goes to confront
my mom right now,

32
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:53,210
her life will be in danger.

33
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:55,550
My mom is already trying
to kill her as it is.

34
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:57,450
She must never find out...

35
00:02:57,820 --> 00:02:59,580
that I met Oh Jang Mi.

36
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:01,290
And what's your name?

37
00:03:02,090 --> 00:03:05,760
- I'm Seo Rin.
- Seo Rin?

38
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:09,590
So, your last name is Seo
and your first name is Rin?

39
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,270
How old are you?

40
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:17,140
We're the same age, aren't we?

41
00:03:18,540 --> 00:03:21,910
Could we be twins?

42
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:26,010
Twins? With you?

43
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:27,010
That's ridiculous.

44
00:03:28,110 --> 00:03:29,110
Then...

45
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:33,790
A doppelganger.
Maybe it's something like that.

46
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:35,720
A doppelganger?

47
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:40,960
I've only ever seen that in the movies,
never in real life.

48
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:42,390
Same here.

49
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,660
Right.

50
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:50,740
Jang Mi, you'll never guess who I saw.
Someone who looks like you at the...

51
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:54,940
Dad said he saw someone on the street
who looked just like me.

52
00:03:55,410 --> 00:03:57,610
Dad must have seen you.

53
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:01,750
You've seen my dad, haven't you?

54
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:06,020
Look. This is my dad.

55
00:04:11,690 --> 00:04:12,720
So you have seen him.

56
00:04:13,830 --> 00:04:16,090
My dad said he saw you on the street.

57
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:19,930
- Which street was it? Tell me.
- What on earth are you talking about?

58
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:21,770
I've never seen him before.

59
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,700
(Mom)

60
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,210
Aren't you going to get that?

61
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:40,320
Yes? What's up?

62
00:04:40,450 --> 00:04:44,520
- You missed work. Where are you?
- Shit.

63
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,520
I hear you haven't contacted
General Manager Kang.

64
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,460
Do you plan to learn the ropes?

65
00:04:48,530 --> 00:04:50,060
What do you mean, learn the ropes?

66
00:04:50,130 --> 00:04:51,830
Are you not going to work
with General Manager Kang?

67
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:55,270
Why? Does he miss me or something
because I'm not around?

68
00:04:55,370 --> 00:04:56,900
I'm asking you.

69
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,270
Where are you right now?

70
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,810
I was in a foul mood,
so I'm doing a little shopping.

71
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:02,740
Do you really have to butt in
like this all the time?

72
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:05,180
We have the same face,
but we're completely different.

73
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:08,510
It seems like Seo Rin lives
a completely different life from me.

74
00:05:09,080 --> 00:05:10,280
A real-life doppelganger?

75
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,050
Could that really be it?

76
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,650
This is absurd.

77
00:05:14,650 --> 00:05:15,720
Okay, fine.

78
00:05:16,390 --> 00:05:17,460
Don't worry.

79
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:19,760
I won't be posting my luxury goods
on social media or anything.

80
00:05:19,860 --> 00:05:24,030
- Come back here now. Understood?
- Am I a child? Why so controlling?

81
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,200
All right, fine. I'll head back now.

82
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:33,440
- I have to get to the office.
- The office?

83
00:05:34,010 --> 00:05:35,210
Where do you work?

84
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:36,470
Can we...

85
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,540
see each other again?

86
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:42,710
Put your number in. I'll call you.

87
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,280
Okay.

88
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,520
There.

89
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:53,760
Just wait until I call you.

90
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:57,930
You'll really call me, right?
I have so many questions.

91
00:06:02,370 --> 00:06:04,970
We'll see each other again.

92
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:08,270
But you need to wait quietly until then.

93
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:11,110
And don't say a word about this to anyone.

94
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,640
Got it?

95
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,580
Promise me.

96
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,850
It's the only way
we'll see each other again.

97
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:20,790
I don't know why,

98
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,850
but I promise.

99
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:32,830
Hey! Don't forget to call!

100
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:33,900
I'll be waiting!

101
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:39,570
What was that all about?

102
00:06:40,140 --> 00:06:41,810
It feels like I was under a spell.

103
00:06:42,570 --> 00:06:44,940
Gosh, what just happened?

104
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,450
(Law Firm Leeho)

105
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:56,550
Baek Ho. We need to go over
to Oh Jang Mi's house.

106
00:06:56,790 --> 00:06:59,260
- Why Jang Mi's house?
- Why do you think?

107
00:06:59,860 --> 00:07:04,760
Even though the case is closed,
it'll be a huge headache if they appeal.

108
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:10,540
The prosecution would re-examine the case,
and that situation still makes me uneasy.

109
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:11,940
Mom,

110
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:17,010
if you're about to tell me to stop Jang Mi
from filing an appeal,

111
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:18,340
then I don't want to hear it.

112
00:07:18,740 --> 00:07:21,680
Whether or not she files an appeal
is her choice,

113
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:25,120
- it's not my place to get involved.
- I can't believe you!

114
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:27,320
Honestly.

115
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,890
Already wrapped around
some girl's little finger...

116
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:31,660
Unbelievable.

117
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:35,860
- I'm really disappointed in you.
- You raised me to do the right thing.

118
00:07:35,930 --> 00:07:36,930
I know.

119
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:40,230
And that's what makes this
even more infuriating!

120
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:41,570
Seriously...

121
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:43,470
You!

122
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,840
This girl, Oh Jang Mi
or whatever her name is,

123
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,370
just stop obsessing over her.

124
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:51,010
Your father...

125
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:56,080
may not show it, but he was worried sick
about getting a criminal record.

126
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,050
If he ends up with a criminal record,

127
00:07:58,550 --> 00:08:00,250
he'll have to resign
from his professorship.

128
00:08:00,820 --> 00:08:02,520
Is that what you want for your father?

129
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:05,520
No, Mom.
That's a completely different issue.

130
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:07,460
Anyway,

131
00:08:08,090 --> 00:08:10,330
do you have any idea
what your father has been going through?

132
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:15,230
He has to get you and Jun Ho married off,
and what if your father had a record?

133
00:08:16,670 --> 00:08:19,840
That would've been a fatal blow
to your father's reputation.

134
00:08:20,970 --> 00:08:24,210
Gosh, he's such a proud man, deep down.

135
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:31,320
Yes, Dean.

136
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:33,750
Of course.

137
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:36,020
I'm quite all right.

138
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:39,190
Thank you for your concern.

139
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:40,560
Sure.

140
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:43,460
Yes, I'll stop by your office soon, Dean.

141
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:45,460
Okay.

142
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:04,780
Will Oh Jang Mi really fall
for this whole doppelganger story?

143
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:10,150
No. She's probably just like me,
so she's bound to figure it out.

144
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:14,730
Oh my...

145
00:09:15,730 --> 00:09:17,300
What's going on? Where's my mother?

146
00:09:18,130 --> 00:09:19,460
Good grief.

147
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:21,500
Must be nice to be you.

148
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:25,040
Coming and going from work
whenever you please.

149
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:26,800
Shit.

150
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:29,870
Team Leader Jin,
were you saying that for me to hear?

151
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:33,910
Of course not.
I was just talking to myself.

152
00:09:34,310 --> 00:09:36,980
Watch it. I'm not in a good mood lately.

153
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:39,150
What a temper.

154
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,720
Seo Rin?

155
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,830
Who is she? Where does she live?

156
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,800
How can she look exactly like me?

157
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:54,870
This is so confusing.

158
00:09:55,430 --> 00:09:57,370
I don't understand any of this.

159
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,770
Could I be a twin?

160
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,970
I wonder if Mom knows.

161
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:06,140
If we're twins, Mom would have to know.

162
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:13,420
I'm heading to my part-time job.
Give Bo Ra a snack after kindergarten.

163
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:14,750
- Okay.
- Thanks.

164
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:17,020
Tae Sook, I was just...

165
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,820
We'll see each other again.

166
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:22,730
But you need to wait quietly until then.

167
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:25,660
And don't say a word about this to anyone.

168
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,160
Got it?

169
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,070
Promise me.

170
00:10:29,770 --> 00:10:31,400
It's the only way
we'll see each other again.

171
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:35,270
What is it? What were you about to say?

172
00:10:35,540 --> 00:10:38,080
It's nothing. Have a good day.

173
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,650
Good luck!

174
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:53,090
Mom.

175
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:55,560
Are you putting the bunnies to bed?

176
00:10:57,090 --> 00:11:01,030
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are pretty,
and Tok Hee is sleeping.

177
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:03,200
Mom, by any chance...

178
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,140
Do I have a twin?

179
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,770
Tok Hee is sleeping.

180
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,580
My Ok Hee and Tok Hee.

181
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:17,310
I saw a woman today
who looked exactly like me.

182
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,150
It was so bizarre.

183
00:11:20,450 --> 00:11:23,390
But then again,
there's no way I could be a twin.

184
00:11:24,090 --> 00:11:25,460
I guess she's my doppelganger.

185
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:29,530
But still,
how could she look exactly like me?

186
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,530
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are pretty.

187
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:33,600
Jang Mi is pretty.

188
00:11:39,970 --> 00:11:43,140
I'm Grandpa's biological granddaughter,
right?

189
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:47,650
So that means
Mom must have tricked Grandpa.

190
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:50,550
Hey, sweetheart. Why aren't you eating?

191
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,550
You have to eat up to stay healthy.

192
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,190
I know, Grandpa.

193
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,720
But if I want to wear pretty clothes,
I can't gain weight.

194
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:02,530
Oh my.
If I want to fit into my wedding dress,

195
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:05,730
- I'd better stop eating.
- Shit. I just lost my appetite.

196
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:09,230
Grandpa, are you
really going to marry her?

197
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,570
Listen to you.

198
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:14,000
It's a done deal.
Everything's already been agreed.

199
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,240
- Why make trouble close to the wedding?
- Everything's been agreed?

200
00:12:17,610 --> 00:12:19,240
Who said anyone agreed?

201
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:21,580
Chairman.

202
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:23,580
No, darling, please.

203
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:26,950
Father, your wedding suit is ready.

204
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:38,330
Right. There's no way someone like Grandpa
wouldn't have done a DNA test.

205
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:40,230
So then Mom...

206
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:43,670
forged the DNA test results
to trick Grandpa?

207
00:12:45,770 --> 00:12:48,240
I just don't know.

208
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,280
My goodness, Seo Rin.

209
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,120
What's with all the drinking?

210
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:03,850
- Goodness, you'll get addicted.
- Shit.

211
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,460
Mind your own business.

212
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:13,060
The nerve.

213
00:13:18,470 --> 00:13:19,970
Hong Ju.

214
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:23,570
Haven't you noticed something's off
with Seo Rin lately?

215
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,840
Seo Rin?

216
00:13:25,410 --> 00:13:26,410
Not really.

217
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:28,950
I'm telling you,
my gut feeling tells me...

218
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:32,980
something's happened to Seo Rin.

219
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:36,190
But I just don't know what.

220
00:13:36,290 --> 00:13:38,460
When have your hunches ever been right?

221
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,360
Right.

222
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:43,930
The police came looking for CEO Chae
a while back.

223
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:47,160
Maybe that's why
Seo Rin's been acting this way.

224
00:13:47,230 --> 00:13:48,900
What? Tell me about it.

225
00:13:49,430 --> 00:13:50,430
Never mind.

226
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:54,040
Professor Kang caused the accident
that killed Oh Jang Mi's dad,

227
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,670
but what could that have to do
with Seo Rin?

228
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:58,040
So I guess that's not it.

229
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:01,310
Wait, why did the police go to see
Chae Hwa Young?

230
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:03,180
It was probably about the car accident.

231
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,820
A car accident is one thing,

232
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:06,980
but why would the police
investigate CEO Chae?

233
00:14:07,050 --> 00:14:10,250
Since Professor Kang caused the accident,
maybe as a person of interest or...

234
00:14:11,190 --> 00:14:12,890
I don't really know.

235
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:14,260
Professor Kang?

236
00:14:16,030 --> 00:14:18,400
Oh my gosh! You're right!

237
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:20,530
- What is?
- Do you remember...

238
00:14:20,530 --> 00:14:23,470
that I said CEO Chae
was probably seeing Professor Kang...

239
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:28,170
and I even took that picture
of them together?

240
00:14:28,340 --> 00:14:29,340
Yes, I remember.

241
00:14:29,710 --> 00:14:32,810
But the Chairman and CEO Chae
swore up and down it wasn't true.

242
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:36,710
So then why, when it comes to
Professor Kang's accident,

243
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,720
is CEO Chae being investigated?
Why is that?

244
00:14:40,780 --> 00:14:42,820
I have no idea.

245
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:45,160
This feels so sketchy.

246
00:14:45,690 --> 00:14:47,590
There's definitely something more to this.

247
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,300
Come on.

248
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:55,700
Drink it all down.

249
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,870
- I'm home.
- Good grief...

250
00:14:59,870 --> 00:15:02,240
- Hey.
- You're just getting home?

251
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:05,610
Dad, you've been through a lot,
haven't you?

252
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:08,180
A rough time? It was nothing.

253
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:12,120
Listen up.
Don't any of you ever drink and drive.

254
00:15:12,420 --> 00:15:15,790
And don't drive late at night.
Just take a cab.

255
00:15:16,390 --> 00:15:20,690
You're so worn down from all this.
My one and only.

256
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,790
Oh my goodness, your lovey-dovey romance.

257
00:15:24,530 --> 00:15:26,630
You boys should watch and learn.

258
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:30,130
So hurry up and bring home some fiancees,
you hear me?

259
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:34,200
Baek Ho, Oh Jang Mi is
absolutely out of the question.

260
00:15:34,510 --> 00:15:35,740
I'm making myself perfectly clear.

261
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:39,310
With such bad blood between the families,
I'm sure Baek Ho knows better.

262
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,680
Right, son?

263
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,710
I didn't hear a thing.

264
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:49,890
Jun Ho, you need to start thinking
about marriage soon, too.

265
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:51,890
Isn't there anyone special?

266
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:53,820
No, there isn't.

267
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:57,430
He was just promoted,
so his mind is probably on work.

268
00:15:57,430 --> 00:15:58,960
How could he have time for dating?

269
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:01,370
Is CEO Chae not giving you
a hard time anymore?

270
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:05,370
Why would she give him a hard time?
She must think highly of him,

271
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,640
or she wouldn't have promoted him
to general manager.

272
00:16:08,510 --> 00:16:10,140
- Is that so?
- Of course.

273
00:16:13,380 --> 00:16:14,380
Okay.

274
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,000
Hello?

275
00:16:41,510 --> 00:16:43,170
Hwa Young, were you asleep?

276
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:45,180
I was just about to.

277
00:16:45,510 --> 00:16:47,880
I don't know if you've heard the news.

278
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:52,080
My case was closed,
and it's a huge weight off my shoulders.

279
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:53,450
That's a relief.

280
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:57,550
Did you happen
to pull some strings for me?

281
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:02,560
Thank you so much. It's all thanks to you.

282
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,730
Honey, have some fruit.

283
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:08,770
Right. I'll stop by tomorrow
to thank you. Okay.

284
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:12,900
What was that?

285
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:16,310
Did he just hang up on me
because his wife walked in?

286
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:22,710
Then again, if I'm going to
marry Seo Rin off to Jun Ho,

287
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:26,350
I'd have to break up with him
at some point anyway.

288
00:17:28,850 --> 00:17:30,520
Still, it stings.

289
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,460
Why are you giving me fruit?
It's time for bed.

290
00:17:36,830 --> 00:17:40,360
You need to eat to regain all the energy
you’ve lost.

291
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:42,270
You really had a hard time.

292
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:45,770
So, who were you just on the phone with?

293
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:48,640
What?

294
00:17:48,870 --> 00:17:51,910
Who did you call so late at night
just to say you’re stopping by tomorrow?

295
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:55,680
Oh, right. It was Professor Kim.

296
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:59,520
Honey, are you trying
to get into my business?

297
00:18:00,420 --> 00:18:05,160
- Alright, here you go. Open your mouth.
- I said I already brushed my teeth.

298
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,160
Come on.

299
00:18:07,390 --> 00:18:08,460
This is actually good.

300
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:12,430
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

301
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:17,700
Tae Pyung.

302
00:18:18,840 --> 00:18:21,170
- Jang Mi.
- Why do you keep hanging around here?

303
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,110
You're not welcome here.

304
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:25,610
I have something really important
to tell Jang Mi today.

305
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:30,180
Do you remember that prize drawing
we entered a while back?

306
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:32,120
A prize drawing?

307
00:18:33,350 --> 00:18:34,850
I want to buy another outfit for Bo Ra.

308
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:36,320
- Where was that store?
- We're giving away a brand-new TV!

309
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:38,390
- Enter now!
- A children's store is that way.

310
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:40,890
We're giving away a brand-new TV.
Enter now!

311
00:18:41,260 --> 00:18:43,460
- We're giving away a new TV! Enter now!
- Thanks.

312
00:18:43,690 --> 00:18:44,700
So cute!

313
00:18:45,230 --> 00:18:47,160
Hey, should we enter?

314
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:49,730
But it says only couples can enter.

315
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:52,940
- Come on, we're a couple.
- We are?

316
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,240
Come on, we can just say we're a couple.
What's the big deal?

317
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:59,880
If we win first prize, we do get a TV.

318
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:02,550
Couldn't we sell it
and buy my dad a new suit?

319
00:19:02,650 --> 00:19:04,380
That's what I'm saying. Let's do it.

320
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:06,420
We're giving away a brand-new TV.
Enter now!

321
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:07,420
(Electroland)

322
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,690
We're giving away a brand-new TV!

323
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:12,560
Yes, I remember. But why?

324
00:19:12,620 --> 00:19:15,260
I just got a call saying
we won the couple's event.

325
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,360
The prize drawing?

326
00:19:17,460 --> 00:19:20,360
The one where you could win a TV?

327
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:24,540
- Yes.
- But we're not even a couple.

328
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,870
Don't say that. Just go and get it.

329
00:19:27,340 --> 00:19:29,140
You could at least sell that
to help pay things off.

330
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:40,950
Hi, we got a call saying we were winners.

331
00:19:42,590 --> 00:19:46,020
Alright, everyone,
our first winning couple has arrived!

332
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:47,520
Oh my!

333
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:52,860
Listen, lately, a lot of people
are faking being a couple for the prizes,

334
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,870
so we can't skip
the couple's verification test!

335
00:19:55,170 --> 00:19:59,100
We're going to start a quiz mission
to see if you two are a real couple!

336
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:03,040
Well... We were just told
we won the grand prize.

337
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:06,380
Don't tell me you're not a couple.
If you're not, you can forget the prize.

338
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:08,310
We can't just give the prize away
to anyone.

339
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:11,150
This is a promotion exclusively
for newly married couples.

340
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:12,650
So, what are you going to do?

341
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:15,550
- Should we just call this a forfeit?
- No.

342
00:20:16,550 --> 00:20:19,290
We are a couple. We'll do it.

343
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:23,290
Let's just wing it.

344
00:20:25,860 --> 00:20:27,000
Then let's begin.

345
00:20:27,970 --> 00:20:31,340
Where did the two of you first meet?

346
00:20:32,270 --> 00:20:33,270
One, two...

347
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:36,970
- Are you going to let go or not?
- I'm not letting go.

348
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:41,310
- Goodness, thanks a lot.
- Oh, my.

349
00:20:45,050 --> 00:20:46,380
One, two, three!

350
00:20:46,450 --> 00:20:47,620
- Dream Department Store!
- In front of Dream Department Store!

351
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:51,120
Good enough!

352
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:53,390
- They're pretty good.
- Alright, next question.

353
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:56,960
What is your boyfriend's favorite food?

354
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:06,040
Have you been starving or something?

355
00:21:06,370 --> 00:21:09,470
We've eaten together a million times,
but I've never seen you eat like this.

356
00:21:09,540 --> 00:21:12,280
Jang Mi, your cooking is the best.

357
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:14,510
My mom made the japchae.

358
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:18,620
Japchae is my specialty.
Jung Suk Hee makes a mean japchae.

359
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:19,720
Oh, really?

360
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:22,390
One, two, three!

361
00:21:22,450 --> 00:21:23,450
- Japchae!
- Japchae!

362
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:27,390
You didn't rehearse this beforehand,
did you?

363
00:21:27,460 --> 00:21:28,860
- Not at all.
- No, of course not.

364
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:31,160
All right, here's the final question.

365
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:35,570
What's your girlfriend's favorite animal?

366
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:39,940
And this one's for you, Jang Mi.

367
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:44,170
- This little thing? What is it?
- It's a lucky hippo.

368
00:21:44,470 --> 00:21:47,610
In Northern Europe, a hippo doll
means good luck and prosperity.

369
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:53,820
One, two, three!

370
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,890
- A hippo?
- A hippo?

371
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:59,190
You two are a real couple!

372
00:22:00,060 --> 00:22:01,320
Congratulations!

373
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:05,300
Is this it?

374
00:22:07,530 --> 00:22:10,070
Oh my goodness!

375
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:17,440
(CEO's Office)

376
00:22:23,410 --> 00:22:24,450
Mom.

377
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:27,080
Mom, you had a bad cold,

378
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,320
but you got better right away
after taking your medicine, didn't you?

379
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:33,560
Mom, you need to make sure you bundle up
so you don't get sick again, okay?

380
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:36,060
Jang Mi, you're so pretty.

381
00:22:36,060 --> 00:22:38,530
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

382
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:41,430
That's right. I'm your daughter, Mom.

383
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:46,240
No! I refuse to live my life
like Oh Jang Mi.

384
00:22:49,210 --> 00:22:50,210
Mom.

385
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:54,710
Oh my...

386
00:22:55,010 --> 00:22:57,710
My amazing mom. You're always on my side,

387
00:22:57,780 --> 00:23:01,450
- and you know me better than anyone.
- What has gotten into you?

388
00:23:02,350 --> 00:23:03,990
I just love how you smell.

389
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:06,160
Who are you really, Mom?

390
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,530
You're scaring me.

391
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:09,860
You're spying on me?

392
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:13,800
I can't breathe.
Why are you being so clingy?

393
00:23:14,260 --> 00:23:16,130
Why are you acting so out of character?

394
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:18,600
Anyway, have a seat.

395
00:23:22,340 --> 00:23:25,110
Why have you been drinking so much lately?

396
00:23:25,810 --> 00:23:27,010
Is something going on?

397
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:29,580
It's nothing.
And since when am I not a drinker?

398
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:32,180
At least I didn't offer to buy a round
for the entire bar yesterday.

399
00:23:32,450 --> 00:23:33,550
Aren't I good, Mom?

400
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:36,250
Were you drinking
with General Manager Kang the other night?

401
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:40,260
Why do you think I'm all over you now?
It's not for nothing.

402
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:44,930
- So, how far have you two gone?
- Why would you ask me that?

403
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:46,960
No comment on that front.

404
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:50,130
Silly girl.
As if you could hide anything from me.

405
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:53,700
Jun Ho and I are getting married soon.

406
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:58,040
- And I'm going to take bridal classes.
- What? You are?

407
00:23:58,180 --> 00:24:00,440
I'm marrying the man I love,

408
00:24:00,610 --> 00:24:03,210
so of course I want to make him happy.
Don't you agree?

409
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:08,220
I want to do right by him.
And if I want to make him happy,

410
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:10,650
then taking these classes
is the natural next step.

411
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,860
Good. That's a very good idea.

412
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:15,860
For once, you're actually putting
my mind at ease.

413
00:24:17,430 --> 00:24:21,630
And since Grandpa is marrying
Yeom San Wol,

414
00:24:21,770 --> 00:24:26,270
you, me, and Jun Ho will have to
present a united front, right?

415
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,570
Look at the clever little fox.

416
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:32,080
Now I don't have to worry about a thing.

417
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:34,850
That's my girl. You're so smart.

418
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:37,250
That's why I adore you so much.

419
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:42,650
Okay. I will uncover everything...

420
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:44,790
about how you stole me.

421
00:24:49,790 --> 00:24:50,790
Tae Sook.

422
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:54,230
Here, for the rent.

423
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:57,070
What's all this?

424
00:24:57,800 --> 00:25:00,000
Jang Mi, did you win the prize?

425
00:25:02,070 --> 00:25:03,070
A prize?

426
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:06,880
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

427
00:25:10,210 --> 00:25:11,680
My dear Ok Hee is sleeping.

428
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:15,220
Ok Hee is sleeping so peacefully.

429
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:18,920
My dear Tok Hee is sleeping.

430
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:21,520
Tok Hee is fast asleep.

431
00:25:21,930 --> 00:25:24,190
<i>Rock-a-bye, rock-a-bye</i>

432
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:26,860
"Ok Hee and Tok Hee..."

433
00:25:28,470 --> 00:25:30,730
Mom. By any chance...

434
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:32,900
Do I have a twin?

435
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:34,840
What?

436
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:40,540
Did you have another baby like me?
Mom, try to remember. Please?

437
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:44,010
You really don't remember anything at all?

438
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:50,090
My dear Ok Hee is sleeping.

439
00:25:50,890 --> 00:25:52,820
My dear Tok Hee is sleeping.

440
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:56,760
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are sleeping
so peacefully.

441
00:25:58,130 --> 00:26:00,230
They're so pretty.

442
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:02,630
Jang Mi is so pretty.

443
00:26:03,030 --> 00:26:04,830
Mom, am I Ok Hee,

444
00:26:05,740 --> 00:26:07,140
and my sister is Tok Hee?

445
00:26:08,070 --> 00:26:09,640
Is that why...

446
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:11,780
you've been calling the bunnies
Ok Hee and Tok Hee?

447
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:13,980
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are sleeping.

448
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:17,780
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

449
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:20,250
Jang Mi is so pretty.

450
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,620
Ok Hee and Tok Hee are so pretty.

451
00:26:26,460 --> 00:26:27,460
Jang Mi.

452
00:26:28,990 --> 00:26:30,160
Listen to me carefully.

453
00:26:32,030 --> 00:26:33,930
The one who did that to your mother...

454
00:26:35,930 --> 00:26:36,930
and you...

455
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,040
You...

456
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:42,310
Ssangkal...

457
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:47,240
Dad was trying to tell me I have a twin.

458
00:26:47,980 --> 00:26:51,150
He was trying to tell me I have a twin
even in his final moments.

459
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:55,090
Does the person who did this to Mom...

460
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:58,190
have something to do
with me having a twin?

461
00:27:24,350 --> 00:27:25,750
(The First Man)

462
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:28,950
- I think I need to meet with CEO Chae.
- You mean CEO Chae Hwa Young?

463
00:27:29,350 --> 00:27:30,390
What for?

464
00:27:30,690 --> 00:27:32,160
Why are you so worked up?

465
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:34,390
Excuse me, do you recognize this person?

466
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:37,160
I can't let Kang Baek Ho run into Seo Rin.

467
00:27:37,590 --> 00:27:41,100
He's the man who bought soju
near Jang Mi's father's accident scene.

468
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:43,370
- Do you know who he is?
- Who's your mother?

469
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,740
How about we trade lives?

470
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:49,970
Maybe that person has something to do
with my mom's accident.

471
00:27:50,570 --> 00:27:51,810
All right, let's do it.

472
00:27:52,910 --> 00:27:54,910
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
